  "text": "Since we have 160 barcodes for each lesion, we choose to sum the 160 distances to create a vector of size 132 for each lesion. This vector can then be used in traditional machine learning algorithms. We choose to use an implementation of the support vector machine (SVM) called LibSVM to test the classification accuracy on various subsets of the data with the one-dimensional and two-dimensional filtrations [CITATION_1] .",
